Why Pytorch?
It helps builds the model.
It helps in training the model
It helps in making predictions
It helps in fixing errors.

Model:
It takes input, and make predictions.
Training:
Using data model adapts the patterns to make guess.
Training loop:
Get train -> check mistakes -> try to fix it and repeat it.
Prediction:
Result/Output of model.
Loss:
How much wrong is model.
Optimizer:
Fix the model after finding the loss.
Parameters:
These are the number that model learns and adjust to fix the loss.
Batch:
While training we dont feed all data at once. We split the data into smaller chunks. That chunks is batch.
Epoch:
It means model has seen all training data how many times.
